1
00:02:18,014 --> 00:02:19,431
ROBIN:
I want a car.

2
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:23,435
Chicks dig the car.

3
00:02:23,728 --> 00:02:26,396
This is why Superman works alone.

4
00:02:34,572 --> 00:02:38,366
Do try and bring this one
back in one piece, sir!

5
00:03:08,314 --> 00:03:09,606
Don't wait up, Al.

6
00:03:09,774 --> 00:03:11,816
I'll cancel the pizzas.

7
00:03:17,448 --> 00:03:20,450
[SIGHING]

8
00:03:26,499 --> 00:03:27,624
[BEEPS]

9
00:03:27,792 --> 00:03:31,628
Batman, a new villain has
commandeered the Gotham Museum.

10
00:03:31,837 --> 00:03:33,713
He's frozen the antiquities wing.

11
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:36,341
He's turned
the security guards into ice.

12
00:03:36,509 --> 00:03:38,843
He's calling himself, "Mr. Freeze."

13
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:40,845
Mr. Freeze.

14
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,746
MAN 1: Stop!
MAN 2: Drop your weapon!

15
00:04:06,956 --> 00:04:08,248
MAN 3:
Stop or we'll shoot!

16
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,041
[GUNSHOTS]

17
00:04:21,846 --> 00:04:23,680
The Iceman cometh.

18
00:04:25,182 --> 00:04:27,517
Please, show some mercy.

19
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,018
Mercy?!

20
00:04:31,188 --> 00:04:36,025
I'm afraid that my condition has
left me cold to your pleas of mercy.

21
00:04:54,295 --> 00:04:55,879
In this universe...

22
00:04:56,088 --> 00:04:58,548
...there's only one absolute.

23
00:05:00,384 --> 00:05:02,177
Everything...

24
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:04,053
...freezes.

25
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:11,686
Hi, Freeze. I'm Batman.

26
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:23,740
[GRUNTING]

27
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,999
You're not sending me to the cooler.

28
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:53,561
-Nice catch.
-You break it, you buy it.

29
00:05:53,771 --> 00:05:56,105
Grab the gem! Kill the heroes!

30
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:59,108
[WHOOPING]

31
00:06:09,453 --> 00:06:12,330
Yes, kill them! Kill them! Yes!

32
00:06:13,415 --> 00:06:15,625
Destroy everything!

33
00:06:26,345 --> 00:06:27,971
It's the hockey team from hell.

34
00:07:02,673 --> 00:07:05,383
You get the ice, I'll get the Iceman.

35
00:07:19,815 --> 00:07:21,149
[SCREAMING]

36
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:25,945
Ah.

37
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:28,656
[WHIMPERING]

38
00:07:31,452 --> 00:07:32,994
MR. FREEZE:
Thanks.

39
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:50,219
Sweet.

40
00:07:54,892 --> 00:07:57,560
I got mine. Where's yours?

41
00:07:59,063 --> 00:08:00,855
MR. FREEZE:
What killed the dinosaurs?

42
00:08:01,565 --> 00:08:03,441
The Ice Age!

43
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:13,368
[RUMBLING]

44
00:08:55,577 --> 00:08:56,786
Hit me, boys.

45
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,541
Thanks for playing.

46
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:30,319
I was hoping you'd drop in.

47
00:10:03,645 --> 00:10:05,480
MR. FREEZE:
Oh, yes.

48
00:10:28,337 --> 00:10:29,545
Watch the numbers...

49
00:10:29,713 --> 00:10:32,215
...for they are
the harbingers of your doom.

50
00:10:32,382 --> 00:10:33,549
Can you feel it coming?

51
00:10:33,717 --> 00:10:36,803
The icy cold of space.

52
00:10:38,305 --> 00:10:42,016
At 30,000 feet,
your heart will freeze...

53
00:10:42,226 --> 00:10:44,393
...and beat no more.

54
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:57,740
After you're frozen, your icy tomb
will plummet back to Gotham.

55
00:10:57,908 --> 00:10:59,325
Freeze, you're mad.

56
00:11:00,244 --> 00:11:02,328
This capsule explodes,
it'll slaughter thousands.

57
00:11:02,538 --> 00:11:03,621
Freeze well.

58
00:11:15,384 --> 00:11:16,676
[PANTING]

59
00:11:27,396 --> 00:11:29,689
BATMAN: Who invited you?
-I was hanging around.

60
00:11:29,857 --> 00:11:32,692
I thought you'd stay in the museum,
round up some thugs.

61
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:35,528
How about, "Nice to see you.
Thanks for saving my life."

62
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:50,960
-A batbomb?
-We must blow this up...

63
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:53,421
...before it turns Gotham into a crater.

64
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,630
[BEEPING]

65
00:11:54,798 --> 00:11:56,549
ROBIN:
Now what, call a taxi?!

66
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,050
Watch the first step!

67
00:11:59,303 --> 00:12:00,386
Surf's up!

68
00:12:05,601 --> 00:12:06,934
[BEEPING]

69
00:12:35,339 --> 00:12:36,672
ROBIN:
Gotcha!

70
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:44,221
Cowabunga!

71
00:13:02,741 --> 00:13:05,201
He's freezing the furnace!

72
00:13:45,701 --> 00:13:48,077
-I got him.
BATMAN: Robin, no!

73
00:13:54,084 --> 00:13:56,836
MR. FREEZE:
Stay cool, Birdboy.

74
00:14:06,555 --> 00:14:10,099
Can you be cold?
You have 11 minutes to thaw the bird.

75
00:14:10,434 --> 00:14:13,602
Will you chase the villain
or save the boy?

76
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:14,895
[LAUGHS]

77
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:18,774
Your emotions make you weak.
That's why this day is mine.

78
00:14:20,444 --> 00:14:22,278
I'll kill you next time!

79
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,491
Did we get him?

80
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,919
[THUNDER CRASHING]

81
00:15:22,339 --> 00:15:23,339
PAMELA:
Drats!

82
00:15:23,507 --> 00:15:28,469
My experiment to mate the orchid
and the rattlesnake has failed again...

83
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:33,682
...but I still have hope for
the animal-plant crossbreedings.

84
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:37,645
If I can only find
the right dose of venom...

85
00:15:37,813 --> 00:15:41,398
...these plants will be able to
fight back, like animals.

86
00:15:42,192 --> 00:15:43,984
I will have given flora...

87
00:15:44,194 --> 00:15:48,697
...a chance against
the thoughtless ravages of man.

88
00:15:48,949 --> 00:15:50,699
[MAN SCREAMING]

89
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:53,369
Personal note:

90
00:15:53,912 --> 00:15:55,871
My work would proceed faster...

91
00:15:56,039 --> 00:15:59,333
...if Dr. Woodrue didn't whisk
my venom samples...

92
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:02,711
...back to his mysterious
Gilgamesh Wing.

93
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:05,548
Why won't he let me in the lab?

94
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,174
[MAN SCREAMING]

95
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:09,844
What is he doing in there?

96
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:31,448
WOODRUE: Ladies and gentlemen
of the un-United Nations...

97
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:36,245
...and our mystery bidder...

98
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,497
...may I present...

99
00:16:38,707 --> 00:16:41,041
...Antonio Diego...

100
00:16:41,209 --> 00:16:45,588
...serial murderer,
serving life in prison...

101
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:47,756
...and sole surviving...

102
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:49,008
...volunteer.

103
00:16:49,176 --> 00:16:51,093
[WOODRUE LAUGHING]

104
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:53,095
And what a charmer he is.

105
00:16:54,264 --> 00:16:58,893
By merely drilling three
concentric holes...

106
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:02,938
...directly into Antonio's
cranial cavity...

107
00:17:03,106 --> 00:17:07,109
...I have created viaducts into
the most primitive part of his brain...

108
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:09,945
...the limbic system.

109
00:17:12,407 --> 00:17:14,283
And now I add...

110
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:17,077
...my Super-Soldier Serum...

111
00:17:17,245 --> 00:17:19,788
...code-named "Venom"...

112
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:23,209
...to which I add
my very own recipe of steroids...

113
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:25,127
...and toxins.

114
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:28,547
Plug him in.

115
00:17:28,757 --> 00:17:30,090
Time to scream.

116
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:41,769
[SCREAMING]

117
00:18:03,917 --> 00:18:05,334
WOODRUE:
Genius!

118
00:18:05,669 --> 00:18:06,752
Behold...

119
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:09,630
...the ideal killing machine!

120
00:18:09,839 --> 00:18:11,966
I call this little number...

121
00:18:12,342 --> 00:18:13,634
..."Bane."

122
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:16,053
Bane of Humanity!

123
00:18:17,097 --> 00:18:18,597
Imagine it.

124
00:18:18,807 --> 00:18:22,559
Your own private army made up of
thousands of these super-soldiers.

125
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:26,939
Bidding begins at a mere
10 million!

126
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:28,524
Turbo!

127
00:18:28,692 --> 00:18:30,192
Show off for Daddy.

128
00:18:30,986 --> 00:18:32,611
[BANE ROARING]

129
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,608
[PAMELA GASPING]

130
00:19:12,152 --> 00:19:13,485
Dr. Isley.

131
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:18,115
Welcome to my parlor.

132
00:19:19,242 --> 00:19:20,701
PAMELA:
What?

133
00:19:20,869 --> 00:19:22,202
You monster!

134
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:23,829
How could you?!

135
00:19:23,997 --> 00:19:27,249
Our original sponsor had
no stomach for military applications.

136
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:30,002
-He cut the funding for our work.
-Our work?

137
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:31,754
Without your research...

138
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:34,590
...I couldn't have come this far.
Join me.

139
00:19:34,758 --> 00:19:39,011
-The two of us, entwined, side by side.
-Join you?

140
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:44,266
I have spent my life trying to
protect plants from extinction...

141
00:19:44,434 --> 00:19:48,354
...and now you corrupt my research...

142
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:52,232
...into some maniacal scheme
for world domination?

143
00:19:53,526 --> 00:19:56,028
When I get through...

144
00:19:56,196 --> 00:20:00,783
...you won't be able to get a job
teaching high school chemistry.

145
00:20:01,034 --> 00:20:02,451
Do you hear me?!

146
00:20:02,619 --> 00:20:05,162
You psycho!

147
00:20:07,123 --> 00:20:10,459
Well, I can respect your opinion.

148
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:13,295
Sadly, I'm not good at rejection.

149
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,547
I'm afraid you'll have to die.

150
00:20:15,715 --> 00:20:17,299
[SCREAMING]

151
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:41,156
Yes. Yes.

152
00:20:41,408 --> 00:20:45,327
Let the poisons and toxins
burn a grave for you...

153
00:20:45,495 --> 00:20:47,996
...deep into the earth
you love so much!

154
00:20:48,248 --> 00:20:49,915
Bye-bye, dear!

155
00:20:50,417 --> 00:20:51,834
Fellow maniacs...

156
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:55,504
...bidding begins!

157
00:21:02,095 --> 00:21:06,348
BRUCE: Gotham University Labs
security video, two years ago.

158
00:21:07,684 --> 00:21:09,184
Dr. Victor Fries...

159
00:21:09,352 --> 00:21:13,689
...two-time Olympic decathlete and
Nobel Prize winner for molecular biology.

160
00:21:13,857 --> 00:21:17,317
After his wife contracted a rare disease,
Macgregor's Syndrome...

161
00:21:17,485 --> 00:21:21,280
...he hoped to freeze her in a cryogenic
sleep until he could find a cure.

162
00:21:21,448 --> 00:21:24,116
Now, here's where
everything goes north.

163
00:21:26,369 --> 00:21:27,744
[SCREAMING]

164
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:32,332
That's got to hurt.

165
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,169
BRUCE:
That liquid is 50 below.

166
00:21:35,336 --> 00:21:37,129
But he survived somehow.

167
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:40,466
The cryo-solution mutated his body.

168
00:21:45,305 --> 00:21:47,806
DICK: What happened to his wife?
-Nobody knows for sure.

169
00:21:47,974 --> 00:21:49,475
She's presumed dead.

170
00:21:49,642 --> 00:21:51,560
Fries needs
extreme cold to survive.

171
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:56,732
His cryo-suit uses diamond-enhanced
lasers to keep him at 0 degrees.

172
00:21:58,067 --> 00:22:01,069
If it's ice the Iceman wants....

173
00:22:03,239 --> 00:22:07,826
Alfred.

174
00:22:11,581 --> 00:22:12,915
ALFRED:
Coming, sir.

175
00:22:14,501 --> 00:22:15,918
Yes, sir?

176
00:22:16,085 --> 00:22:17,753
We need the Wayne diamonds.

177
00:22:18,004 --> 00:22:19,713
We going to trap a snowman?

178
00:22:20,590 --> 00:22:24,510
Absolutely, right after you spend
10 hours in the simulator, training.

179
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:28,180
I made a mistake. I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

180
00:22:28,348 --> 00:22:30,390
You were reckless
and almost got killed.

181
00:22:30,558 --> 00:22:32,893
I'm fine! See!
Me, here, alive!

182
00:22:33,228 --> 00:22:36,104
How we supposed to work together
if you won't trust me?

183
00:22:39,317 --> 00:22:41,109
How indeed?

184
00:22:41,736 --> 00:22:44,112
BRUCE:
He's overeager, he's impulsive.

185
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:46,323
I can't trust him not to get hurt.

186
00:22:46,950 --> 00:22:50,452
Perhaps the truth is
you really don't trust anyone.

187
00:22:50,954 --> 00:22:53,956
Don't tell me
you're on his side again.

188
00:22:54,624 --> 00:22:57,042
Despite all your talents...

189
00:22:57,252 --> 00:23:00,379
...you're still just
a novice in the ways of family.

190
00:23:00,588 --> 00:23:04,132
Master Dick follows
the same star as you...

191
00:23:04,342 --> 00:23:07,261
...but gets there by his own course.

192
00:23:07,971 --> 00:23:11,598
You must learn to trust him,
for that is the nature of family.

193
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,434
I trust you, Alfred.

194
00:23:15,478 --> 00:23:18,105
But I shan't be here forever.

195
00:23:21,359 --> 00:23:23,151
Good night, Master Bruce.

196
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:26,989
Good night, Alfred.

197
00:23:47,468 --> 00:23:49,428
ALFRED:
Oh, dear, Master Bruce.

198
00:23:49,637 --> 00:23:52,014
Good gracious, what a tumble.

199
00:23:52,307 --> 00:23:54,391
There's a brave boy.

200
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:08,530
Yes, sir. I am so pleased you won
the bidding, Your Supreme Ruthlessness.

201
00:24:08,698 --> 00:24:11,867
We're making the final modifications
on Bane right now.

202
00:24:12,035 --> 00:24:16,913
We'll have a flawless super-soldier
out to you tomorrow by overnight mail.

203
00:24:17,165 --> 00:24:19,041
[RUMBLING]

204
00:24:38,019 --> 00:24:39,853
WOODRUE:
Dr. Isley?

205
00:24:40,730 --> 00:24:43,565
-Pamela?
-Mm-hm.

206
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:45,192
You look great.

207
00:24:45,735 --> 00:24:47,944
Especially for a dead woman.

208
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:51,073
Hello, Jason.

209
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,910
I think I've had a change of heart.

210
00:24:55,203 --> 00:24:57,829
-Or quite literally...
-Me?

211
00:24:57,997 --> 00:25:03,001
...the animal-plant toxins had
a rather unique effect on me.

212
00:25:03,169 --> 00:25:05,837
They replaced my blood with aloe...

213
00:25:06,047 --> 00:25:09,091
...my skin with chlorophyll...

214
00:25:09,258 --> 00:25:10,884
...and filled...

215
00:25:11,094 --> 00:25:13,095
...my lips...

216
00:25:13,596 --> 00:25:15,097
[POISON IVY MOANS]

217
00:25:24,065 --> 00:25:25,482
...with venom.

218
00:25:27,485 --> 00:25:28,777
Oh...

219
00:25:29,028 --> 00:25:30,987
...and, Jason, one other thing.

220
00:25:31,906 --> 00:25:35,492
I probably should have
mentioned this earlier...

221
00:25:36,494 --> 00:25:37,911
...I'm...

222
00:25:38,496 --> 00:25:39,788
...poison.

223
00:25:39,997 --> 00:25:41,206
[SCREAMING]

224
00:25:43,292 --> 00:25:45,293
Whoo.

225
00:25:46,587 --> 00:25:48,296
It's a jungle in here.

226
00:25:49,882 --> 00:25:51,508
I am Nature's arm...

227
00:25:52,385 --> 00:25:54,052
...her spirit...

228
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:56,555
...her will!

229
00:25:57,056 --> 00:25:59,474
Hell, I am Mother Nature.

230
00:25:59,642 --> 00:26:01,643
And the time has come...

231
00:26:01,811 --> 00:26:03,645
...for plants to take back...

232
00:26:03,896 --> 00:26:06,648
...the world so rightfully ours...

233
00:26:06,899 --> 00:26:08,400
...because it's not nice...

234
00:26:09,736 --> 00:26:12,779
...to fool with Mother Nature.

235
00:26:17,952 --> 00:26:20,579
Hmm. "Wayne Enterprises."

236
00:26:21,038 --> 00:26:22,414
[BANE ROARING]

237
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:27,043
Coming, Bane, darling.

238
00:26:27,545 --> 00:26:29,296
We've got a plane to catch.

239
00:26:38,598 --> 00:26:39,973
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

240
00:26:40,141 --> 00:26:42,684
[SINGING ON TV]
I'm Mr. White Christmas

241
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:44,770
I'm Mr. Snow

242
00:26:45,104 --> 00:26:47,689
I'm Mr. Icicle

243
00:26:48,065 --> 00:26:49,858
I'm Mr. Ten Below

244
00:26:50,067 --> 00:26:51,443
MR. FREEZE:
Sing! Sing!

245
00:26:55,823 --> 00:26:57,115
[MEN SINGING]

246
00:26:57,283 --> 00:26:59,075
MR. FREEZE:
Come on, sing!

247
00:27:00,286 --> 00:27:01,661
Louder! Come on!

248
00:27:01,829 --> 00:27:03,705
Sing, sing, sing! Come on!

249
00:27:03,873 --> 00:27:05,624
MEN [SINGING]:
He's Mr. White Christmas

250
00:27:05,833 --> 00:27:07,375
MR. FREEZE:
Come on, louder!

251
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:10,712
MEN [SINGING]:
He's Mr. Icicle

252
00:27:11,798 --> 00:27:13,215
WOMAN:
Freezy...

253
00:27:13,633 --> 00:27:15,383
...I'm feeling hot.

254
00:27:15,635 --> 00:27:17,594
-I find that unlikely.
-Okay.

255
00:27:18,304 --> 00:27:21,723
So my hair is brittle
and my skin is dry...

256
00:27:21,974 --> 00:27:24,184
...I'd weather blizzards to have you.

257
00:27:24,352 --> 00:27:27,062
You're the most perfect man
I've ever known.

258
00:27:27,230 --> 00:27:29,356
What do you say we heat things up?

259
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:32,067
My passion thaws
for my bride alone.

260
00:27:33,903 --> 00:27:36,238
Talk about your cold shoulder.

261
00:27:41,410 --> 00:27:42,702
Frosty!

262
00:27:42,912 --> 00:27:44,079
Yeah, boss?

263
00:27:44,247 --> 00:27:46,498
MR. FREEZE:
Ah. Energy.

264
00:27:47,667 --> 00:27:50,252
Battling the Bat
exhausted my power.

265
00:27:55,091 --> 00:27:56,424
But...

266
00:27:57,343 --> 00:27:59,678
...I was successful nevertheless.

267
00:28:00,847 --> 00:28:02,222
Absolutely, boss.

268
00:28:02,431 --> 00:28:04,933
One more giant diamond of this size...

269
00:28:05,184 --> 00:28:08,186
...and my freezing engine
will be complete.

270
00:28:11,357 --> 00:28:12,691
I will freeze the city.

271
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:16,069
Then I will hold Gotham ransom.

272
00:28:16,279 --> 00:28:18,655
Unless the city bows
to my demands...

273
00:28:18,865 --> 00:28:20,615
...it's winter forever
in Gotham.

274
00:28:21,284 --> 00:28:23,660
The city fathers
will have no choice...

275
00:28:23,870 --> 00:28:27,789
...but to give me the billions
I need to complete my research...

276
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,127
...so I can find a cure.

277
00:28:33,462 --> 00:28:34,796
Leave us.

278
00:28:35,047 --> 00:28:36,172
Sure, boss.

279
00:28:38,301 --> 00:28:40,468
MR. FREEZE:
We need quality time.

280
00:28:56,986 --> 00:28:59,905
Soon we will be together
once more.

281
00:29:00,907 --> 00:29:02,490
Soon.

282
00:29:18,341 --> 00:29:19,758
[DOORBELL RINGS]

283
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:22,844
BRUCE:
Alfred.

284
00:29:23,346 --> 00:29:24,971
[DOORBELL RINGS]

285
00:29:25,431 --> 00:29:26,848
DICK:
I'll get it.

286
00:29:36,943 --> 00:29:39,694
I must've dozed off.
My sincerest apologies.

287
00:29:39,946 --> 00:29:41,529
No apology necessary.

288
00:29:41,739 --> 00:29:44,491
It's the first time it's happened
in 30 years.

289
00:29:57,546 --> 00:29:59,047
Please be looking for me.

290
00:29:59,548 --> 00:30:02,384
Actually, I'm looking for
Alfred Pennyworth.

291
00:30:03,052 --> 00:30:04,844
Uncle Alfred.

292
00:30:06,889 --> 00:30:08,515
Uncle Alfred!

293
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:10,058
Oh, my dear.

294
00:30:10,267 --> 00:30:12,018
Oh, my dear...

295
00:30:12,228 --> 00:30:14,688
...what a most wonderful surprise.

296
00:30:14,897 --> 00:30:17,857
How did you manage
to come here all the way from England?

297
00:30:18,067 --> 00:30:21,236
My dear, you are so kind
to your old uncle.

298
00:30:21,404 --> 00:30:22,821
[WHISPERS]
Uncle?

299
00:30:25,783 --> 00:30:29,244
ALFRED: Barbara is the daughter
of my dear sister Margaret.

300
00:30:29,787 --> 00:30:33,206
BARBARA: Both my parents were killed
in a car accident five years ago.

301
00:30:33,416 --> 00:30:35,750
Uncle Alfred's been supporting me
ever since.

302
00:30:35,918 --> 00:30:37,711
-You have?
DICK: Secrets, Al?

303
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:42,048
Secrets are a virtual prerequisite
in this house.

304
00:30:42,258 --> 00:30:43,925
Don't you think, sir?

305
00:30:44,343 --> 00:30:45,427
I'm on break from--

306
00:30:45,594 --> 00:30:48,596
Oxbridge Academy,
Alfred's alma mater.

307
00:30:48,931 --> 00:30:51,766
The new computer sciences division.

308
00:30:51,934 --> 00:30:54,936
-How'd you know?
-Says so on the patch on your sweater.

309
00:30:58,357 --> 00:30:59,941
BARBARA:
Oh.

310
00:31:00,109 --> 00:31:03,611
-What is it? It's beautiful.
-You can say that again.

311
00:31:04,071 --> 00:31:05,447
It's a competition racer.

312
00:31:05,614 --> 00:31:07,073
-I've been fixing it up.
-Really?

313
00:31:07,241 --> 00:31:10,452
DICK: I'll show you how to ride it.
ALFRED: You certainly will not!

314
00:31:10,619 --> 00:31:14,247
BARBARA: Don't worry, Uncle Alfred.
I'm terrified of these things.

315
00:31:14,457 --> 00:31:16,624
BRUCE:
Barbara, I hope you'll stay with us.

316
00:31:17,334 --> 00:31:18,793
Oh, I don't know.

317
00:31:18,961 --> 00:31:22,130
All this luxury really isn't
my style, but...

318
00:31:22,965 --> 00:31:24,132
...yeah, I'd love to.

319
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,134
Then it's settled.

320
00:31:26,635 --> 00:31:28,803
Oh, but, sir, we....

321
00:31:29,138 --> 00:31:31,306
We do get so busy here.

322
00:31:31,474 --> 00:31:32,640
Don't be silly.

323
00:31:32,808 --> 00:31:34,642
After all, she's family.

324
00:31:50,242 --> 00:31:51,576
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

325
00:31:51,744 --> 00:31:52,869
BARBARA:
Uncle Alfred?

326
00:31:54,997 --> 00:31:56,831
I came to tuck you in.

327
00:31:56,999 --> 00:31:59,334
You came to tuck me in?

328
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:01,336
That's quite a switch.

329
00:32:01,504 --> 00:32:04,130
Yes. What're you working on?

330
00:32:04,340 --> 00:32:07,842
I'm trying to find my brother,
your Uncle Wilfred.

331
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:11,971
He's first butler
to the Maharajah of Miranjapore.

332
00:32:12,181 --> 00:32:15,141
But Miranjapore is a floating court.

333
00:32:15,351 --> 00:32:17,143
It travels through India.

334
00:32:17,353 --> 00:32:19,187
BARBARA:
Oh, I remember Mom getting postcards.

335
00:32:19,396 --> 00:32:22,524
ALFRED: So Wilfred can be
rather difficult to find.

336
00:32:23,859 --> 00:32:27,028
Well, I don't suppose they have
fax machines on elephants.

337
00:32:28,906 --> 00:32:31,324
I've been trying to reach him
with no success.

338
00:32:32,201 --> 00:32:35,120
When one grows ancient,
one yearns for family.

339
00:32:37,540 --> 00:32:40,416
I have the same picture of Mom
by my bed.

340
00:32:40,668 --> 00:32:41,709
Peg?

341
00:32:41,877 --> 00:32:44,420
My nickname for sweet Margaret.

342
00:32:47,216 --> 00:32:49,384
It's good to see you again.

343
00:32:50,219 --> 00:32:51,302
I've missed you.

344
00:32:52,555 --> 00:32:54,389
As I have you.

345
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:57,183
Sleep well, child.

346
00:32:58,561 --> 00:33:00,061
You sleep.

347
00:33:02,148 --> 00:33:03,898
Go to bed.

348
00:34:08,589 --> 00:34:10,298
GERTY [ON RADIO]:
Good morning, Gotham.

349
00:34:10,507 --> 00:34:15,261
It's Gossip Gerty reporting to you
direct from the Gotham Observatory...

350
00:34:15,471 --> 00:34:19,974
...where billionaire Bruce Wayne,
chairman of Wayne Enterprises...

351
00:34:20,142 --> 00:34:25,146
...is about to make yet another
legendary contribution to the city.

352
00:34:26,315 --> 00:34:28,983
Gotham Observatory, Bane.

353
00:34:29,151 --> 00:34:30,235
And step on it.

354
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:31,819
[BANE GROWLS]

355
00:34:32,029 --> 00:34:33,321
BANE:
Step.

356
00:34:42,164 --> 00:34:46,834
BRUCE: My father told me, "To succeed,
we need only pick a star and follow it."

357
00:34:47,670 --> 00:34:51,839
So Wayne Enterprises is donating
the world's most advanced telescope...

358
00:34:52,049 --> 00:34:55,176
...to Gotham's
Observatory Restoration Project.

359
00:34:55,344 --> 00:34:56,678
With any luck...

360
00:34:56,845 --> 00:34:59,514
...this telescope will give
future generations...

361
00:34:59,682 --> 00:35:02,016
...a chance to follow their own stars.

362
00:35:02,184 --> 00:35:03,643
[APPLAUSE]

363
00:35:04,270 --> 00:35:05,353
GERTY:
Brucy...

364
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:09,649
...is it true that this new telescope
can see around the globe?

365
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:12,568
Yes. If you'll watch these monitors
right here. Doctor Lee?

366
00:35:13,529 --> 00:35:18,199
LEE: Satellites in orbit allow us to reflect
light from anywhere on the planet.

367
00:35:18,701 --> 00:35:22,036
From here, we'll be able
to see the sky anywhere on Earth...

368
00:35:22,204 --> 00:35:24,998
...and through this
intricate network of satellites...

369
00:35:25,207 --> 00:35:29,544
...reflect it back to our
very own Gotham City for observation.

370
00:35:29,712 --> 00:35:31,504
Just don't point it at my bedroom.

371
00:35:31,672 --> 00:35:32,880
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

372
00:35:37,219 --> 00:35:40,013
GERTY: Brucy, you
and the exquisite Julie Madison...

373
00:35:40,180 --> 00:35:41,848
...have been going out forever.

374
00:35:42,057 --> 00:35:44,225
Are you going to tie the knot?

375
00:35:44,393 --> 00:35:45,977
Uh, marriage?

376
00:35:46,145 --> 00:35:47,395
Uh, uh, marriage?

377
00:35:47,604 --> 00:35:49,897
You want to give me a hand here?

378
00:35:50,399 --> 00:35:52,567
Bruce and I are recklessly in love.

379
00:35:52,735 --> 00:35:56,404
And that's most certainly
enough for us. For now.

380
00:35:57,865 --> 00:36:00,908
If you will follow me,
I'll show you the central control grid.

381
00:36:01,243 --> 00:36:02,910
You're a lot of help.

382
00:36:04,747 --> 00:36:05,997
MAN:
Miss, you need to stop.

383
00:36:06,165 --> 00:36:07,540
PAMELA:
Move, fascist bulldog!

384
00:36:07,708 --> 00:36:09,917
-You need an appointment--
-No, I don't!

385
00:36:10,085 --> 00:36:13,046
MAN: Miss, you're not authorized
to be up here.

386
00:36:13,255 --> 00:36:14,422
She has no pass, sir.

387
00:36:14,631 --> 00:36:17,383
BRUCE: Little overly protective,
but you won't hurt me, Miss--?

388
00:36:17,551 --> 00:36:19,135
Dr. Pamela Isley.

389
00:36:19,345 --> 00:36:20,720
Doctor...

390
00:36:20,888 --> 00:36:22,263
...what can I do for you?

391
00:36:22,765 --> 00:36:24,932
Actually, I already
work for you, or did.

392
00:36:25,142 --> 00:36:27,727
Your arboreal preservation project
in South America.

393
00:36:28,437 --> 00:36:31,606
We cut our funding.
There was a conflict of ideologies.

394
00:36:31,774 --> 00:36:33,399
Dr. Woodrue was a lunatic.

395
00:36:33,567 --> 00:36:34,776
I see you knew him.

396
00:36:34,943 --> 00:36:39,113
Yes. That lab burnt down last week.
I'm glad you escaped.

397
00:36:39,281 --> 00:36:43,451
I have here a proposal showing how
Wayne Enterprises can immediately...

398
00:36:43,660 --> 00:36:46,621
...cease all actions
that toxify our environment.

399
00:36:46,789 --> 00:36:49,123
Forget the stars,
look here at the earth...

400
00:36:49,291 --> 00:36:50,917
...our mother, our womb.

401
00:36:51,126 --> 00:36:54,128
She deserves your loyalty
and protection.

402
00:36:54,296 --> 00:36:56,923
And yet, you spoil her lands...

403
00:36:57,466 --> 00:37:00,134
...poison her oceans,
blacken her skies!

404
00:37:00,302 --> 00:37:01,552
You're killing her!

405
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:06,265
Your intentions are noble,
but no diesel fuel for heat...

406
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:08,476
...no coolants to preserve food...

407
00:37:08,685 --> 00:37:11,270
...millions of people would die
of cold and hunger.

408
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:14,190
Acceptable losses
in the battle to save the planet.

409
00:37:15,109 --> 00:37:17,402
People come first, Dr. Isley.

410
00:37:19,196 --> 00:37:20,571
Mammals!

411
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:23,491
A day of reckoning is coming.

412
00:37:23,700 --> 00:37:24,826
That's right.

413
00:37:24,993 --> 00:37:28,621
The same plants and flowers
that saw you...

414
00:37:28,789 --> 00:37:30,790
...crawl from the primordial soup...

415
00:37:30,999 --> 00:37:35,253
...will reclaim this planet
and there will be no one to protect you!

416
00:37:35,796 --> 00:37:37,171
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

417
00:37:37,923 --> 00:37:39,173
You....

418
00:37:39,341 --> 00:37:41,467
You must be new in town.

419
00:37:41,677 --> 00:37:45,138
In Gotham City,
Batman and Robin protect us...

420
00:37:45,347 --> 00:37:48,015
...even from plants and flowers.

421
00:37:51,353 --> 00:37:53,187
Maybe you'd like to meet them.

422
00:37:53,939 --> 00:37:56,232
Caped crusaders are
going to help us auction...

423
00:37:56,442 --> 00:37:59,026
...a diamond to raise money
for our botanical gardens.

424
00:37:59,695 --> 00:38:03,865
Just a few mammals doing what
we can for the world's plants.

425
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:05,658
Thank you all for coming.

426
00:38:05,868 --> 00:38:07,160
Good day, doctor.

427
00:38:16,545 --> 00:38:18,713
Batman and Robin...

428
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:22,675
...militant arm
of the warm-blooded oppressors...

429
00:38:23,469 --> 00:38:27,138
...animal protectors of the status quo.

430
00:38:28,223 --> 00:38:29,682
First...

431
00:38:29,892 --> 00:38:33,561
...I'll rid myself of the fur
and feathered pests.

432
00:38:34,730 --> 00:38:36,856
And then Gotham...

433
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:38,524
...will be mine...

434
00:38:38,734 --> 00:38:40,485
...for the greening.

435
00:38:43,071 --> 00:38:45,072
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE ON TV]

436
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:03,090
Uh, excuse me, chief.

437
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:05,843
I got something here
you might want to see.

438
00:39:12,851 --> 00:39:15,520
I hate when people talk
during the movie.

439
00:39:34,957 --> 00:39:37,124
One more diamond, my love.

440
00:39:38,126 --> 00:39:39,794
One more.

441
00:39:47,135 --> 00:39:49,387
"Bruce Wayne. Diamonds."
Hmm.

442
00:39:51,807 --> 00:39:53,391
Very nice.

443
00:39:55,310 --> 00:39:56,811
[DRUMS BEATING]

444
00:40:06,655 --> 00:40:08,155
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

445
00:40:38,020 --> 00:40:40,771
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentlemen...

446
00:40:40,939 --> 00:40:44,692
...Gossip Gerty
of Good Morning Gotham and I...

447
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:49,113
...welcome you to
the gem of the evening.

448
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:52,408
GERTY:
Our own Commissioner Gordon...

449
00:40:53,035 --> 00:40:57,913
...displaying the famed Heart of Isis,
on loan...

450
00:40:58,123 --> 00:41:02,543
...from the collection of my
close personal friend, Bruce Wayne.

451
00:41:05,881 --> 00:41:08,716
-Think Freeze will take the bait?
-He'll be here.

452
00:41:08,925 --> 00:41:12,720
--to dance with one
of our fabulous flowers...

453
00:41:12,971 --> 00:41:16,557
...the famed diamond
draped around her neck.

454
00:41:19,227 --> 00:41:21,896
GERTY:
Let's start the bidding!

455
00:41:22,397 --> 00:41:24,899
I'll give 10,000 for the orchid!

456
00:41:25,233 --> 00:41:26,651
[PEOPLE GASPING]

457
00:41:27,069 --> 00:41:29,320
MAN:
20,000 for the tiger lily!

458
00:41:31,406 --> 00:41:32,531
And I bid...

459
00:41:32,741 --> 00:41:36,494
...30,000 dollars
for the lovely magnolia!

460
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,584
GERTY:
Boys, please...

461
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:45,670
...let's show some gusto!

462
00:41:45,921 --> 00:41:48,506
[LAUGHS]

463
00:43:52,798 --> 00:43:54,131
Hi there.

464
00:43:54,883 --> 00:43:57,051
And you are?

465
00:43:57,469 --> 00:43:59,178
Poison...

466
00:43:59,387 --> 00:44:00,805
...Poison Ivy.

467
00:44:01,056 --> 00:44:02,681
[PEOPLE GASPING]

468
00:44:08,563 --> 00:44:10,022
POISON IVY:
Mmm.

469
00:44:11,483 --> 00:44:14,235
Why not send junior home early?

470
00:44:14,611 --> 00:44:17,863
I've got some wild oats to sow.

471
00:44:19,574 --> 00:44:21,408
On the other hand...

472
00:44:22,702 --> 00:44:25,412
...youth does have its advantages.

473
00:44:26,248 --> 00:44:28,749
Endurance, stamina.

474
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:31,752
Forget the geriatric bat.

475
00:44:32,128 --> 00:44:33,671
Come, join me.

476
00:44:33,839 --> 00:44:36,131
My garden needs tending.

477
00:44:36,633 --> 00:44:38,092
I'll take it from here, pal.

478
00:44:38,260 --> 00:44:40,427
Wouldn't you like the earrings too?

479
00:44:41,263 --> 00:44:45,432
POISON IVY: Some lucky boy's
about to hit the honey pot.

480
00:44:45,767 --> 00:44:49,854
I'll include an evening of my company
for the winner.

481
00:44:50,647 --> 00:44:52,940
I'll bring everything you see here...

482
00:44:53,191 --> 00:44:56,527
...plus everything you don't.

483
00:44:58,363 --> 00:45:01,282
I bid 50,000 dollars for Poison Ivy!

484
00:45:01,575 --> 00:45:03,576
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

485
00:45:04,202 --> 00:45:06,287
100,000!

486
00:45:07,664 --> 00:45:08,789
And I'll bid...

487
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:12,293
...500,000 dollars!

488
00:45:14,129 --> 00:45:15,296
One million dollars.

489
00:45:16,923 --> 00:45:19,133
-Two million.
-You don't have it. Three million.

490
00:45:19,301 --> 00:45:20,801
I'll borrow it from you. Four.

491
00:45:22,095 --> 00:45:24,763
-Five million.
-That's a utility belt, not a money belt.

492
00:45:24,973 --> 00:45:27,057
-Six million.
-Seven million.

493
00:45:30,604 --> 00:45:31,937
Never leave the cave without it.

494
00:45:32,272 --> 00:45:35,816
You boys aren't going to start
fighting over little me, now, are you?

495
00:45:41,990 --> 00:45:43,282
[SCREAMING]

496
00:45:49,581 --> 00:45:51,790
All right, everyone! Chill.

497
00:45:53,001 --> 00:45:55,628
Chill. Chill.

498
00:45:56,630 --> 00:45:58,297
[SCREAMING]

499
00:46:03,345 --> 00:46:05,012
Get the gun!

500
00:46:31,456 --> 00:46:32,790
Yeah.

501
00:46:41,383 --> 00:46:42,549
Boo.

502
00:46:48,348 --> 00:46:49,890
MR. FREEZE:
Look at you!

503
00:46:50,141 --> 00:46:52,017
Let me guess.

504
00:46:52,644 --> 00:46:53,894
Plant Girl?

505
00:46:54,312 --> 00:46:56,063
Vine Lady?

506
00:46:56,815 --> 00:46:59,066
Hand over the diamond, Garden Gal...

507
00:46:59,275 --> 00:47:01,068
...or I'll turn you into mulch.

508
00:47:06,074 --> 00:47:07,533
Pheromone dust...

509
00:47:08,576 --> 00:47:11,412
...designed to heat a man's blood.

510
00:47:11,830 --> 00:47:14,206
Doesn't work on the cold-hearted.
If you please!

511
00:47:15,250 --> 00:47:17,334
If you insist.

512
00:47:20,839 --> 00:47:23,340
Clever little clover.

513
00:47:23,550 --> 00:47:24,925
MAN:
Whoa!

514
00:47:27,429 --> 00:47:29,596
That's my exit cue.

515
00:47:30,015 --> 00:47:31,390
Thanks.

516
00:47:42,694 --> 00:47:44,069
Good night.

517
00:47:45,947 --> 00:47:47,614
Cool party!

518
00:47:47,782 --> 00:47:49,283
[LAUGHING]

519
00:48:15,101 --> 00:48:18,270
Commissioner, you have 11 minutes
to thaw these people.

520
00:48:24,819 --> 00:48:28,739
Miss Ivy, you've just met
one of the most sinister men in Gotham.

521
00:48:29,157 --> 00:48:31,158
That's not a man...

522
00:48:31,367 --> 00:48:33,368
...that is a god.

523
00:48:39,501 --> 00:48:41,418
Enough monkey business.

524
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:44,505
We've got work to do.

525
00:48:45,381 --> 00:48:46,924
BANE:
Monkey work.

526
00:49:09,114 --> 00:49:11,115
[HORNS HONKING]

527
00:49:37,725 --> 00:49:40,352
-Pull back. You can't make the jump.
-I can make it!

528
00:49:43,148 --> 00:49:45,440
-Pull back!
-I can make it!

529
00:49:45,650 --> 00:49:47,151
Redbird control codes.

530
00:49:50,196 --> 00:49:51,446
Disable engine.

531
00:49:51,656 --> 00:49:52,698
[BEEPING]

532
00:49:52,866 --> 00:49:54,575
ROBIN:
No! Don't do this to me!

533
00:49:54,826 --> 00:49:56,368
No!

534
00:50:02,959 --> 00:50:04,084
We won't make it!

535
00:50:11,926 --> 00:50:13,260
[SCREAMS]

536
00:50:27,233 --> 00:50:29,276
It's a cold town.

537
00:50:41,956 --> 00:50:43,081
[LAUGHS]

538
00:50:43,291 --> 00:50:44,541
Uh-oh.

539
00:51:00,808 --> 00:51:02,309
ROBIN:
I could've made that jump.

540
00:51:02,477 --> 00:51:05,395
You could've splattered your brains
on the building's side.

541
00:51:05,563 --> 00:51:07,231
The Flying Graysons were a team.

542
00:51:07,482 --> 00:51:09,483
We had to trust each person
to do his job.

543
00:51:09,651 --> 00:51:11,652
That's what being partners is about.

544
00:51:11,819 --> 00:51:14,279
Counting on someone
is the way to win.

545
00:51:14,447 --> 00:51:16,740
Your head wasn't on the job.
It was on Poison Ivy.

546
00:51:17,325 --> 00:51:19,576
Maybe she wanted me instead of you.

547
00:51:19,744 --> 00:51:21,453
That's your idea of friendship?

548
00:51:21,663 --> 00:51:24,289
It's your rules.
It's your way, or the highway.

549
00:51:24,499 --> 00:51:27,125
It's Batman and Robin,
not Robin and Batman.

550
00:51:27,335 --> 00:51:30,504
-I'm sick of it!
-Yes, it's my rules that keep us alive.

551
00:51:30,672 --> 00:51:34,049
If you want to stay in this house,
on this team, you'll abide by them.

552
00:51:35,176 --> 00:51:36,802
This is no partnership.

553
00:51:37,011 --> 00:51:38,845
You're never going to trust me!

554
00:51:45,353 --> 00:51:47,187
ALFRED:
Dear brother Wilfred...

555
00:51:47,689 --> 00:51:51,692
...I have tried
every address I know for you.

556
00:51:51,859 --> 00:51:54,194
I'm just praying this reaches you.

557
00:51:55,029 --> 00:51:56,613
We have very little time.

558
00:52:09,294 --> 00:52:10,794
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

559
00:52:13,089 --> 00:52:15,632
ALFRED:
Batman monopolized the evening news.

560
00:52:16,676 --> 00:52:17,718
BRUCE:
Huh. Yes.

561
00:52:17,885 --> 00:52:20,470
Congratulations on your
apprehension of Mr. Freeze.

562
00:52:20,680 --> 00:52:22,222
BRUCE:
Thanks. Thank you.

563
00:52:25,727 --> 00:52:27,352
Is there something wrong, sir?

564
00:52:28,396 --> 00:52:29,855
Alfred...

565
00:52:30,606 --> 00:52:32,190
...am I pig-headed?

566
00:52:32,358 --> 00:52:34,067
Is it...?

567
00:52:34,902 --> 00:52:36,403
Is it always...

568
00:52:36,612 --> 00:52:38,613
...my way or the highway?

569
00:52:38,906 --> 00:52:40,741
Why, yes. Actually.

570
00:52:41,909 --> 00:52:45,662
Death and chance stole your parents...

571
00:52:45,913 --> 00:52:47,914
...but rather than become a victim...

572
00:52:48,166 --> 00:52:52,085
...you have done everything
in your power to control the fates.

573
00:52:52,754 --> 00:52:54,755
For what is Batman...

574
00:52:55,006 --> 00:52:59,676
...if not an effort to master the chaos
that sweeps our world?

575
00:53:00,636 --> 00:53:02,429
An attempt to control...

576
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:04,264
...death itself?

577
00:53:24,202 --> 00:53:25,952
But I can't, can I?

578
00:53:27,538 --> 00:53:29,206
None of us can.

579
00:53:49,644 --> 00:53:50,936
DICK:
Hey!

580
00:53:51,396 --> 00:53:52,979
BARBARA:
Hyah!

581
00:53:55,233 --> 00:53:57,401
Sorry. Um, so sorry!

582
00:53:57,568 --> 00:53:59,194
DICK:
Teach you that at Oxbridge?

583
00:53:59,404 --> 00:54:03,698
Just a few judo lessons.
You know, London's kind of rough.

584
00:54:04,075 --> 00:54:06,451
I suppose you had
a minor in motorbikes also?

585
00:54:08,913 --> 00:54:10,497
Couldn't resist.

586
00:54:10,748 --> 00:54:11,998
It's just so beautiful.

587
00:54:13,084 --> 00:54:15,836
I just took it out for a spin.
I'll clean it tomorrow.

588
00:54:16,254 --> 00:54:18,588
All right? Sorry.

589
00:54:19,257 --> 00:54:21,133
Um, sorry. Good night.

590
00:54:31,352 --> 00:54:32,769
[THUNDER CRASHING]

591
00:55:06,554 --> 00:55:08,763
MAN 1:
Drag him into the cold beam.

592
00:55:10,641 --> 00:55:12,517
Welcome home, Frost Face.

593
00:55:12,727 --> 00:55:15,770
You're the common cold,
and we are the cure.

594
00:55:18,065 --> 00:55:20,567
Allow me to break the ice.

595
00:55:20,902 --> 00:55:23,069
My name is Freeze.

596
00:55:23,321 --> 00:55:25,071
Learn it well...

597
00:55:25,323 --> 00:55:28,158
...for it's the chilling sound
of your doom.

598
00:55:33,331 --> 00:55:35,499
[GROANING]

599
00:55:38,544 --> 00:55:39,920
[MAN 1 CACKLING]

600
00:55:40,087 --> 00:55:44,216
MAN 1: All right, Freezie, you
can't live outside the cold zone.

601
00:55:44,383 --> 00:55:46,343
[DR. FREEZE MOANING]

602
00:55:46,511 --> 00:55:47,886
[MEN LAUGHING]

603
00:55:49,055 --> 00:55:50,597
[GASPING]

604
00:55:55,853 --> 00:55:57,854
MAN 1:
Look at him stew.

605
00:55:59,941 --> 00:56:01,608
MAN 2:
Get used to it.

606
00:56:01,776 --> 00:56:06,363
You're going to be here a very long,
long time.

607
00:56:07,782 --> 00:56:09,324
Sadly...

608
00:56:09,534 --> 00:56:11,952
...you will not live to see it.

609
00:56:12,453 --> 00:56:13,870
[MEN LAUGHING]

610
00:56:19,377 --> 00:56:21,086
Oh, yes.

611
00:56:23,798 --> 00:56:27,384
Batface and Birdbrain turned out
to be much more...

612
00:56:27,593 --> 00:56:29,970
...resistant to my love dust
than expected.

613
00:56:30,137 --> 00:56:34,140
No matter. Next time
I'll just give them a stronger dose.

614
00:56:34,392 --> 00:56:37,435
They'll literally be dying for me.

615
00:56:37,645 --> 00:56:40,605
Hmm. "Turkish baths."

616
00:56:40,815 --> 00:56:42,732
This looks promising.

617
00:56:45,319 --> 00:56:47,153
[BANE ROARING]

618
00:56:49,949 --> 00:56:51,908
[LAUGHING]

619
00:56:54,078 --> 00:56:55,662
[BANE ROARING]

620
00:57:08,175 --> 00:57:09,926
POISON IVY:
Hmm.

621
00:57:10,094 --> 00:57:11,928
A fixer-upper.

622
00:57:12,513 --> 00:57:14,598
But with a certain homey charm.

623
00:57:15,308 --> 00:57:17,517
Ah. A minus!

624
00:57:17,977 --> 00:57:19,686
Current tenants.

625
00:57:19,895 --> 00:57:22,814
Hello, my little pretty, pretty, pretty.

626
00:57:23,024 --> 00:57:24,691
Hello yourself.

627
00:57:25,401 --> 00:57:26,943
You look good enough to eat.

628
00:57:27,653 --> 00:57:29,487
That I am.

629
00:57:30,031 --> 00:57:32,907
Come and get me, if you can.

630
00:57:35,661 --> 00:57:37,329
With pleasure.

631
00:57:57,725 --> 00:57:59,225
Let's redecorate.

632
00:58:08,486 --> 00:58:11,696
I've always hankered
for something on the water.

633
00:58:20,247 --> 00:58:22,248
What is this floor?

634
00:58:29,507 --> 00:58:31,675
It took God seven days...

635
00:58:31,842 --> 00:58:33,968
...to create Paradise.

636
00:58:34,470 --> 00:58:37,180
Let's see if I can do better.

637
00:58:43,604 --> 00:58:45,105
Good babies.

638
00:58:45,272 --> 00:58:47,190
Grow for mommy.

639
00:58:53,197 --> 00:58:54,614
Bane, darling...

640
00:58:54,865 --> 00:58:58,284
...I found a fellow
who strikes my fancy.

641
00:58:58,494 --> 00:59:00,620
A cool customer, yes.

642
00:59:01,706 --> 00:59:03,623
Icy demeanor...

643
00:59:04,208 --> 00:59:05,709
...no question.

644
00:59:06,544 --> 00:59:10,296
But I detect a certain ruthless charm
I may be able to use...

645
00:59:10,506 --> 00:59:12,382
...to my advantage.

646
00:59:13,300 --> 00:59:15,802
Honey, clean up this mess.

647
00:59:16,053 --> 00:59:18,138
We've got company coming.

648
00:59:18,806 --> 00:59:20,140
BANE:
Honey.

649
00:59:20,307 --> 00:59:21,599
Company.

650
00:59:31,235 --> 00:59:32,652
JULIE: Bruce....
-Hmm?

651
00:59:35,072 --> 00:59:38,533
We've been going out
for over a year now, and....

652
00:59:39,827 --> 00:59:41,161
Okay, here it goes.

653
00:59:41,328 --> 00:59:43,580
I want to spend my life with you.

654
00:59:46,834 --> 00:59:48,668
I'm not the marrying kind.

655
00:59:48,836 --> 00:59:51,671
There are things about me
you wouldn't understand.

656
00:59:52,339 --> 00:59:55,091
I know you're a dedicated bachelor.

657
00:59:55,301 --> 00:59:56,676
You've had your wild nights.

658
00:59:57,428 --> 00:59:58,928
"Wild" doesn't....

659
00:59:59,764 --> 01:00:01,264
Doesn't quite cover it.

660
01:00:02,850 --> 01:00:05,351
You'll make someone
a good husband one day...

661
01:00:05,686 --> 01:00:08,188
...but I can't wait forever.

662
01:00:12,193 --> 01:00:15,028
Look, I don't want to pressure you.
Because if I do...

663
01:00:15,196 --> 01:00:17,280
...you'll just shut down.

664
01:00:17,698 --> 01:00:19,282
I know the way you are.

665
01:00:20,868 --> 01:00:22,619
Think about it.

666
01:00:22,870 --> 01:00:25,079
Just promise me you'll think about it.

667
01:00:25,956 --> 01:00:27,373
Okay?

668
01:00:28,375 --> 01:00:30,126
You don't have to answer now.

669
01:00:30,461 --> 01:00:33,087
Just think it over.

670
01:00:33,297 --> 01:00:35,131
Here's some food for thought.

671
01:00:53,984 --> 01:00:55,235
JULIE:
Who's Ivy?

672
01:00:56,904 --> 01:00:59,364
BRUCE: What?
-You just called me "Ivy."

673
01:00:59,573 --> 01:01:00,865
Who's Ivy?

674
01:01:02,159 --> 01:01:03,493
I wish I knew.

675
01:01:06,205 --> 01:01:08,122
DICK:
Enhance detail, 14 to 19.

676
01:01:13,337 --> 01:01:15,004
Who are you?

677
01:01:16,340 --> 01:01:17,674
[BEEPING]

678
01:01:28,936 --> 01:01:30,353
Gotcha!

679
01:01:56,463 --> 01:01:58,131
[CHEERING]

680
01:02:18,193 --> 01:02:19,819
Banker, how much coin to play?

681
01:02:19,987 --> 01:02:21,112
Two and a half.

682
01:02:21,322 --> 01:02:24,240
You're the chick who won
the tunnel run two nights ago!

683
01:02:24,408 --> 01:02:25,491
That'd be me.

684
01:02:25,701 --> 01:02:28,119
That was kid stuff, sweetheart.

685
01:02:28,287 --> 01:02:31,122
Why don't you take your tricycle
and run home?

686
01:02:32,166 --> 01:02:33,791
-Want a side bet?
-How much?

687
01:02:33,959 --> 01:02:35,835
-How much you got?
-How much you got?

688
01:02:36,003 --> 01:02:39,297
All right, let's race! Come on!

689
01:02:47,222 --> 01:02:50,516
SPIKE: Just make sure the guys
are ready at the end of the bridge.

690
01:02:51,685 --> 01:02:53,019
You got it, Spike!

691
01:03:07,493 --> 01:03:08,534
[GUNSHOT]

692
01:03:39,400 --> 01:03:40,817
Go, go, go!

693
01:03:41,527 --> 01:03:43,069
Watch your left!

694
01:04:02,423 --> 01:04:04,298
SPIKE:
Out of my way, losers!

695
01:04:05,592 --> 01:04:08,302
Nice try, girlie! You're next!

696
01:04:10,347 --> 01:04:11,764
Excuse me!

697
01:04:15,394 --> 01:04:16,936
Look out, baby!

698
01:04:32,703 --> 01:04:33,953
[HORN HONKING]

699
01:04:35,831 --> 01:04:37,957
Not bad for a chick!

700
01:05:11,492 --> 01:05:12,992
Now!

701
01:05:26,882 --> 01:05:28,424
End of the line, sweetheart!

702
01:05:41,146 --> 01:05:42,480
[BARBARA SCREAMING]

703
01:05:54,868 --> 01:05:56,452
So this is where you hang out.

704
01:05:58,622 --> 01:05:59,914
[MOANS]

705
01:06:00,958 --> 01:06:02,291
DICK:
How long you been racing?

706
01:06:02,501 --> 01:06:04,544
BARBARA:
Since my parents died.

707
01:06:04,711 --> 01:06:08,714
I guess all the speed and danger
helped take me out of myself.

708
01:06:08,924 --> 01:06:10,675
Made the pain go away.

709
01:06:11,218 --> 01:06:12,844
You wouldn't understand.

710
01:06:13,053 --> 01:06:14,554
DICK:
You'd be surprised.

711
01:06:14,930 --> 01:06:19,559
BARBARA: Street racing isn't exactly
an acceptable major at Oxbridge...

712
01:06:19,726 --> 01:06:21,185
...so they kicked me out.

713
01:06:21,478 --> 01:06:25,064
But I've already won the money I need
to do what I've always dreamed.

714
01:06:25,315 --> 01:06:27,316
Don't say you want to join the circus.

715
01:06:28,402 --> 01:06:32,530
Alfred has supported me my whole life
and I'm going to pay him back.

716
01:06:33,365 --> 01:06:36,033
I'll take him away
from this dismal life of servitude.

717
01:06:36,869 --> 01:06:38,369
What are you talking about?

718
01:06:38,579 --> 01:06:41,330
Listen, this whole
master-servant thing...

719
01:06:41,540 --> 01:06:42,915
...it's really ridiculous.

720
01:06:43,083 --> 01:06:45,418
Alfred is a sweet, noble man...

721
01:06:45,586 --> 01:06:49,088
...and he's subjugated all his life
and dreams to someone else.

722
01:06:49,256 --> 01:06:51,257
DICK:
Alfred and Bruce are like family.

723
01:06:52,384 --> 01:06:54,594
Paying someone
to prepare your meals...

724
01:06:54,761 --> 01:06:57,680
...do laundry, clean dishes,
you call that family?

725
01:06:57,890 --> 01:06:59,265
DICK:
Alfred's happy.

726
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:00,975
Happy?

727
01:07:01,602 --> 01:07:04,020
You honestly don't know, do you?

728
01:07:04,188 --> 01:07:06,731
How he's hiding the pain all the time.

729
01:07:07,482 --> 01:07:08,774
Alfred's sick.

730
01:07:12,362 --> 01:07:14,280
BRUCE:
Alfred's not sick.

731
01:07:14,615 --> 01:07:15,990
He's dying.

732
01:07:18,702 --> 01:07:20,119
Dying?

733
01:07:23,248 --> 01:07:24,790
Why didn't he tell us?

734
01:07:25,626 --> 01:07:27,960
You know Alfred,
he'd never say anything.

735
01:07:34,259 --> 01:07:35,635
But I can tell.

736
01:07:40,599 --> 01:07:42,308
I can't believe it.

737
01:07:43,810 --> 01:07:45,102
I know.

738
01:08:28,146 --> 01:08:29,814
[PHONE RINGING]

739
01:08:30,691 --> 01:08:32,608
MAN 1:
Cellblock.

740
01:08:33,485 --> 01:08:35,194
Icehead, you got a visitor.

741
01:08:35,821 --> 01:08:38,197
Your sister is here to see you.

742
01:08:38,365 --> 01:08:39,657
Sister?

743
01:08:43,787 --> 01:08:45,705
Brother, dear...

744
01:08:46,331 --> 01:08:48,457
...I heard you were blue.

745
01:08:50,877 --> 01:08:53,212
Don't mind us, ma'am.

746
01:08:53,380 --> 01:08:55,381
You can speak freely.

747
01:08:58,093 --> 01:09:00,594
I don't mind you at all.

748
01:09:04,516 --> 01:09:05,850
Men...

749
01:09:06,018 --> 01:09:08,644
...the most absurd of God's creatures.

750
01:09:08,812 --> 01:09:10,396
We give you life...

751
01:09:11,106 --> 01:09:14,483
...and we can take it away
just as easily.

752
01:09:14,651 --> 01:09:16,902
MAN 1: Right!
MAN 2: Whatever.

753
01:09:18,238 --> 01:09:20,865
I really am to die for.

754
01:09:36,423 --> 01:09:37,757
[SCREAMING]

755
01:09:48,727 --> 01:09:50,269
Impressive!

756
01:09:51,396 --> 01:09:54,732
Well, I, my most
unabominable snowman...

757
01:09:55,275 --> 01:09:57,693
...have been impressed by you.

758
01:09:57,903 --> 01:09:59,278
In fact...

759
01:09:59,446 --> 01:10:01,906
...I propose a pairing.

760
01:10:02,074 --> 01:10:03,407
Hmm.

761
01:10:03,950 --> 01:10:05,451
[BANE ROARING]

762
01:10:12,042 --> 01:10:14,043
I've come to set you free.

763
01:10:15,087 --> 01:10:16,962
An enticing offer...

764
01:10:17,589 --> 01:10:20,925
...but what does the lady
want in return?

765
01:10:22,928 --> 01:10:27,181
Let's cool it for now.
I've got someone I want you to meet.

766
01:10:34,606 --> 01:10:36,941
His name is Bane.

767
01:10:37,484 --> 01:10:40,945
A laundry service that delivers! Wow!

768
01:10:45,617 --> 01:10:48,786
What are you,
about a 50, big and tall?

769
01:10:48,954 --> 01:10:52,456
No, I always go a size smaller.
Makes me look slimmer.

770
01:10:52,624 --> 01:10:53,749
[BANG]

771
01:10:56,169 --> 01:10:57,670
[BEEPING]

772
01:10:58,338 --> 01:10:59,922
I'm running on empty.

773
01:11:00,132 --> 01:11:01,674
I need the diamonds.

774
01:11:01,842 --> 01:11:03,968
I'll help you grab your rocks.

775
01:11:07,347 --> 01:11:09,849
Bane, dear...

776
01:11:10,016 --> 01:11:11,725
...an exit, please.

777
01:11:14,020 --> 01:11:15,438
[BANE ROARS]

778
01:11:17,524 --> 01:11:19,108
Reinforced steel.

779
01:11:19,276 --> 01:11:20,609
Not good.

780
01:11:31,496 --> 01:11:34,790
MR. FREEZE:
Always winterize your pipes.

781
01:11:41,882 --> 01:11:43,257
[SCREAMS]

782
01:11:50,015 --> 01:11:53,976
While I get my diamonds,
you and meatloaf retrieve my wife.

783
01:11:54,186 --> 01:11:57,313
-You never mentioned a wife!
-Come on.

784
01:11:57,522 --> 01:11:59,398
I hope Mr. Bane can swim.

785
01:12:10,994 --> 01:12:12,369
[GUNSHOTS]

786
01:12:17,918 --> 01:12:19,919
BRUCE:
Alfred, are you well?

787
01:12:20,253 --> 01:12:22,755
As well as can be expected, sir.

788
01:12:24,925 --> 01:12:26,425
My friend, I know you're sick.

789
01:12:26,593 --> 01:12:28,427
I can get you the best doctors.

790
01:12:28,595 --> 01:12:31,305
I have seen the best doctors.

791
01:12:31,806 --> 01:12:36,435
A gentleman does not discuss
his ailments. It is not civilized.

792
01:12:36,937 --> 01:12:41,106
I hope that I have taught you
at least that much, Master Bruce.

793
01:12:41,691 --> 01:12:43,067
Alfred...

794
01:12:44,444 --> 01:12:45,945
...have you ever...

795
01:12:46,112 --> 01:12:48,614
...regretted your life working here?

796
01:12:49,449 --> 01:12:50,908
Looking after heroes?

797
01:12:51,117 --> 01:12:52,368
No, sir.

798
01:12:53,328 --> 01:12:57,623
My only regret is that I was never
able to be out there with you.

799
01:13:00,961 --> 01:13:03,337
Not all the heroes wear masks.

800
01:13:07,592 --> 01:13:08,884
Freeze has escaped!

801
01:13:15,642 --> 01:13:16,976
[SIRENS WAILING]

802
01:13:22,649 --> 01:13:25,150
We got this off
the Arkham surveillance camera.

803
01:13:28,488 --> 01:13:29,780
ROBIN:
Poison Ivy.

804
01:13:31,408 --> 01:13:32,491
Two nights ago...

805
01:13:32,659 --> 01:13:36,745
...Gotham Airport, these two arrive
by charter from South America.

806
01:13:37,163 --> 01:13:40,124
They put 10 security guards
in the hospital...

807
01:13:40,333 --> 01:13:44,837
...left a businessman dead from
organic poisoning, stole his limousine.

808
01:13:45,088 --> 01:13:48,340
This is definitely the same pair
that sprang Freeze.

809
01:13:48,508 --> 01:13:51,010
MAN: Commissioner Gordon.
-Excuse me, gentlemen.

810
01:13:51,928 --> 01:13:54,346
Poison Ivy, why would
she help Freeze escape?

811
01:13:54,514 --> 01:13:56,140
She's definitely evil.

812
01:13:56,349 --> 01:13:59,143
She was all I could think about,
like I was in love, but--

813
01:13:59,352 --> 01:14:01,478
I know, then the feeling vanished.

814
01:14:01,688 --> 01:14:04,023
I can't believe
we fought over a bad guy.

815
01:14:04,190 --> 01:14:06,525
Bad, yes. Guy, no.

816
01:14:06,693 --> 01:14:08,485
Well, I'm totally over her.

817
01:14:08,695 --> 01:14:10,404
Me too. Definitely.

818
01:14:11,364 --> 01:14:13,365
-Great stems, though.
-Buds too.

819
01:14:13,533 --> 01:14:16,035
Yeah, those are nice. Here we go.

820
01:14:22,208 --> 01:14:23,375
ROBIN:
It's Nora Fries.

821
01:14:23,543 --> 01:14:24,918
BATMAN:
She's still alive.

822
01:14:40,894 --> 01:14:43,729
He adapted his freezing technology
to reverse the disease.

823
01:14:43,938 --> 01:14:46,482
He even found a cure for the disease
in some stages.

824
01:14:47,525 --> 01:14:48,567
There she is.

825
01:14:49,861 --> 01:14:52,237
POISON IVY: Get the diamonds.
I'll rescue your bride.

826
01:14:52,447 --> 01:14:54,239
We'll meet back at my place.

827
01:14:54,407 --> 01:14:58,744
No. In my weakened condition,
I'm no match for the bat and bird.

828
01:14:58,953 --> 01:15:01,455
You leave those boys to me.

829
01:15:01,915 --> 01:15:03,332
Go!

830
01:15:05,460 --> 01:15:08,212
ROBIN: Can he save her?
-Her case is too advanced.

831
01:15:08,421 --> 01:15:09,755
But maybe someday...

832
01:15:09,964 --> 01:15:11,590
...with more research....

833
01:15:13,259 --> 01:15:14,551
[SNIFFING]

834
01:15:18,098 --> 01:15:19,431
ROBIN:
Poison Ivy.

835
01:15:29,567 --> 01:15:31,694
I hate uninvited guests.

836
01:15:36,574 --> 01:15:37,866
MAN:
My lungs!

837
01:15:38,910 --> 01:15:40,494
My lungs are freezing!

838
01:15:40,704 --> 01:15:42,121
[COUGHING]

839
01:15:53,425 --> 01:15:55,718
Chilled to perfection.

840
01:16:03,017 --> 01:16:04,059
No beauty.

841
01:16:04,477 --> 01:16:05,811
[BANE ROARING]

842
01:16:06,980 --> 01:16:08,522
Just the beast.

843
01:16:28,501 --> 01:16:30,544
Hey, there, pretty birdie.

844
01:16:30,754 --> 01:16:32,671
Give yourself up. If you surrender--

845
01:16:32,839 --> 01:16:34,256
To you?

846
01:16:36,050 --> 01:16:38,010
Polly want a kiss?

847
01:16:50,356 --> 01:16:54,693
There's something about
an anatomically correct...

848
01:16:54,944 --> 01:16:59,031
...rubber suit
that puts fire in a girl's lips.

849
01:17:02,368 --> 01:17:05,829
Why are all the gorgeous ones
homicidal maniacs? Is it me?

850
01:17:05,997 --> 01:17:08,791
Enough sweet talk.

851
01:17:09,000 --> 01:17:10,375
BATMAN:
Oh, no.

852
01:17:11,711 --> 01:17:15,047
First you'll tell me where Freeze is,
then you're going to jail.

853
01:17:19,385 --> 01:17:20,844
I'm a lover, not a fighter.

854
01:17:21,054 --> 01:17:24,389
That's why every Poison Ivy
Action Figure comes with him!

855
01:17:27,894 --> 01:17:30,729
Try not to make a mess when you die.

856
01:17:34,692 --> 01:17:36,026
[COUGHING]

857
01:17:59,717 --> 01:18:01,093
MR. FREEZE:
Yes, yes.

858
01:18:01,761 --> 01:18:02,928
MAN:
Hold it right there!

859
01:18:22,949 --> 01:18:24,074
[BANE'S SUIT BEEPING]

860
01:18:24,617 --> 01:18:25,951
Stop!

861
01:18:28,288 --> 01:18:31,915
Living in the shadow
of the big, bad bat.

862
01:18:32,125 --> 01:18:33,959
You don't need him.

863
01:18:34,794 --> 01:18:36,920
You're the star.

864
01:18:37,130 --> 01:18:38,922
I can see it now:

865
01:18:39,132 --> 01:18:43,302
Your own big, bright signal in the sky.

866
01:18:44,137 --> 01:18:46,138
Let me guide you.

867
01:18:46,389 --> 01:18:47,764
[BANE ROARING]

868
01:18:54,814 --> 01:18:56,648
Let me kiss you.

869
01:18:56,816 --> 01:18:58,317
BATMAN:
Stop! Don't kiss her.

870
01:18:58,985 --> 01:19:01,820
The victim at the airport,
toxins introduced orally.

871
01:19:01,988 --> 01:19:04,656
-What are you saying?
-Why does she want to kiss us?

872
01:19:04,824 --> 01:19:07,284
-I bet her lips are poisoned.
-Poisoned kiss?

873
01:19:07,493 --> 01:19:08,827
You have issues with women!

874
01:19:08,995 --> 01:19:11,496
You can't stand that
she'd kiss me and not you.

875
01:19:11,706 --> 01:19:13,790
Something would be mine, not yours.

876
01:19:24,344 --> 01:19:25,427
POISON IVY:
Exit, Bane.

877
01:19:25,803 --> 01:19:27,346
BANE:
Exit!

878
01:19:38,441 --> 01:19:40,859
Ivy's right. I don't need your help.

879
01:19:43,196 --> 01:19:44,863
I'm going solo!

880
01:19:47,533 --> 01:19:50,452
What happened?
How'd they get away?

881
01:20:05,468 --> 01:20:06,802
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

882
01:20:07,887 --> 01:20:10,889
POISON IVY:
I've never been good with competition.

883
01:20:12,892 --> 01:20:16,061
Who needs a frigid wife anyway?

884
01:20:41,087 --> 01:20:42,921
Make yourself right at home.

885
01:20:45,216 --> 01:20:46,591
Where's my wife?

886
01:20:47,051 --> 01:20:50,095
There was nothing I could do.
Batman deactivated her.

887
01:20:50,596 --> 01:20:52,723
-She's dead.
-You lie!

888
01:20:57,437 --> 01:20:59,229
Oh, no.

889
01:21:17,623 --> 01:21:19,124
I'm sorry.

890
01:21:21,461 --> 01:21:24,379
Their bones will turn to ice!

891
01:21:26,466 --> 01:21:29,134
Their blood will freeze in my hands!

892
01:21:29,969 --> 01:21:31,428
Kill them, of course.

893
01:21:31,637 --> 01:21:33,472
But why stop there?

894
01:21:34,140 --> 01:21:36,933
Why should only
Batman and Robin die...

895
01:21:37,143 --> 01:21:40,562
...while the society that created them
goes unpunished?

896
01:21:40,772 --> 01:21:42,481
Yes!

897
01:21:42,648 --> 01:21:44,816
If I must suffer...

898
01:21:44,984 --> 01:21:47,944
...humanity will suffer with me!

899
01:21:48,154 --> 01:21:52,991
I shall repay them for sentencing me
to a life without human comfort.

900
01:21:53,659 --> 01:21:56,995
I will blanket the city
in endless winter!

901
01:21:57,371 --> 01:21:58,497
First...

902
01:21:59,999 --> 01:22:01,166
...Gotham.

903
01:22:02,335 --> 01:22:03,877
And then...

904
01:22:04,128 --> 01:22:05,462
...the world!

905
01:22:05,880 --> 01:22:08,673
Just what I had in mind.

906
01:22:09,884 --> 01:22:13,136
Everything dead on Earth except us.

907
01:22:13,346 --> 01:22:14,846
A chance for...

908
01:22:15,014 --> 01:22:17,891
...Mother Nature to start again.

909
01:22:18,184 --> 01:22:22,020
Behold, the dawn of a new age.

910
01:22:25,525 --> 01:22:28,693
My mutant plants have the strength
of the deadliest animals.

911
01:22:29,529 --> 01:22:33,907
Once you have frozen mankind,
these babies will overrun the globe.

912
01:22:34,909 --> 01:22:36,701
And we shall rule them.

913
01:22:38,412 --> 01:22:39,871
For we will be...

914
01:22:40,039 --> 01:22:42,707
...the only two people
left in the world.

915
01:22:43,543 --> 01:22:45,210
Yes.

916
01:22:45,545 --> 01:22:47,212
Adam...

917
01:22:48,047 --> 01:22:49,548
...and Evil.

918
01:22:49,715 --> 01:22:51,216
Yes.

919
01:22:51,384 --> 01:22:53,343
MR. FREEZE:
You distract the bat and bird...

920
01:22:53,553 --> 01:22:55,053
...while I prepare...

921
01:22:55,221 --> 01:22:56,638
...to freeze...

922
01:22:56,889 --> 01:22:58,265
...Gotham!

923
01:23:12,780 --> 01:23:15,907
It's stage one
of Macgregor's Syndrome.

924
01:23:16,492 --> 01:23:17,909
I'm sorry.

925
01:23:18,744 --> 01:23:21,580
All we can do is
make him comfortable.

926
01:23:24,083 --> 01:23:25,417
DICK:
Thank you, doctor.

927
01:23:42,768 --> 01:23:45,604
DICK: Macgregor's Syndrome is
what Fries' wife had.

928
01:23:45,771 --> 01:23:48,648
BRUCE: Alfred's condition is
less severe. Fries' research said...

929
01:23:48,816 --> 01:23:51,151
...he cured a case like it,
just didn't say how.

930
01:23:51,319 --> 01:23:53,236
DICK:
No one else is even close.

931
01:23:53,446 --> 01:23:57,073
I'm late for the dedication,
then I go after Freeze and Ivy alone.

932
01:23:57,283 --> 01:23:59,576
-Like hell you do.
-Don't push me right now.

933
01:23:59,785 --> 01:24:02,996
Or what? No one can
capture Ivy but the big, bad bat?

934
01:24:03,164 --> 01:24:05,957
Yeah, right.
You want her for yourself, don't you?

935
01:24:06,167 --> 01:24:09,836
I want her so badly, I can taste it.
That's the whole point.

936
01:24:10,671 --> 01:24:15,133
She's done something to us.
She has us fighting over her somehow.

937
01:24:15,301 --> 01:24:18,678
I know she loves me and not you,
and it's driving you crazy.

938
01:24:18,846 --> 01:24:21,306
That's why you
stopped us from kissing.

939
01:24:21,474 --> 01:24:25,018
-You're not thinking straight.
-But I am.

940
01:24:25,186 --> 01:24:27,145
For the first time in a long time.

941
01:24:27,355 --> 01:24:29,856
I want a Robin signal
in the sky, all right?

942
01:24:30,066 --> 01:24:32,025
I'm tired of living in your shadow.

943
01:24:32,193 --> 01:24:33,485
All that ends now.

944
01:24:38,574 --> 01:24:40,325
I'm sorry, Uncle.

945
01:24:41,661 --> 01:24:43,328
I was too late.

946
01:24:49,001 --> 01:24:50,377
You must....

947
01:24:54,215 --> 01:24:56,841
You must do something for me.

948
01:24:59,011 --> 01:25:00,971
Find my brother, Wilfred...

949
01:25:01,180 --> 01:25:04,975
...your uncle, wherever he is
and give him this.

950
01:25:05,184 --> 01:25:08,895
I have duties
that he must fulfill in my stead.

951
01:25:10,356 --> 01:25:12,857
Only family can be trusted.

952
01:25:13,734 --> 01:25:15,235
What is it?

953
01:25:15,403 --> 01:25:18,863
It is a sacred trust of two good men...

954
01:25:19,115 --> 01:25:22,200
...whom I have the honor
of calling "sir."

955
01:25:25,121 --> 01:25:28,206
Take it to Wilfred,
and I implore you...

956
01:25:29,125 --> 01:25:30,667
...never open it.

957
01:25:34,130 --> 01:25:37,340
You look so like your mother.

958
01:25:40,553 --> 01:25:43,388
GERTY:
Bonsoir, glamorous Gothamites.

959
01:25:43,639 --> 01:25:45,557
Everyone who's anyone...

960
01:25:45,725 --> 01:25:47,434
...has flocked to the Observatory...

961
01:25:47,643 --> 01:25:51,771
...and tonight's star-studded
dedication of the new telescope.

962
01:25:52,064 --> 01:25:53,565
[APPLAUSE]

963
01:25:56,652 --> 01:26:00,071
And here's the man
of the hour himself...

964
01:26:00,281 --> 01:26:02,282
...Bruce Wayne.

965
01:26:02,908 --> 01:26:05,118
MAN 1:
Mr. Wayne, how about a statement?

966
01:26:05,286 --> 01:26:06,536
BRUCE:
Excuse me.

967
01:26:06,704 --> 01:26:08,872
MAN 2: Over here, Mr. Wayne.
MAN 3: Bruce! Bruce!

968
01:26:09,457 --> 01:26:10,540
BRUCE:
Commissioner.

969
01:26:10,708 --> 01:26:12,250
GORDON: How are you?
BRUCE: Good.

970
01:26:12,418 --> 01:26:15,170
-How are you?
-How are you? Good to see you, Bruce.

971
01:26:17,590 --> 01:26:18,882
Young man.

972
01:26:19,425 --> 01:26:22,177
Hello, Gerty. Lovely to see you again.

973
01:26:27,558 --> 01:26:28,933
GORDON:
Thank you.

974
01:26:29,268 --> 01:26:32,103
PAMELA: Commissioner Gordon.
-Yes?

975
01:26:33,439 --> 01:26:35,106
I've always wondered...

976
01:26:35,316 --> 01:26:39,110
...where does
that big old batlight come from?

977
01:26:44,992 --> 01:26:47,410
Why, it's...

978
01:26:47,620 --> 01:26:49,788
...on top of Police Headquarters.

979
01:26:50,706 --> 01:26:53,750
I'd just love to see it.

980
01:26:53,959 --> 01:26:56,419
But you probably don't have access.

981
01:26:56,629 --> 01:26:57,837
Why, dear lady...

982
01:26:58,964 --> 01:27:01,299
...I am the police commissioner.

983
01:27:01,509 --> 01:27:04,469
I have the keys
right here in my pocket.

984
01:27:04,720 --> 01:27:06,221
Would you like to see it?

985
01:27:19,735 --> 01:27:20,985
[SNIFFING]

986
01:27:24,824 --> 01:27:27,826
Who are you, dear lady?

987
01:27:30,663 --> 01:27:33,498
On second thought,
you're way too old for me.

988
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:35,375
No, I'm not.

989
01:27:36,544 --> 01:27:38,002
Please...

990
01:27:38,254 --> 01:27:39,879
...come back.

991
01:27:46,554 --> 01:27:48,680
What are you doing? Come on.

992
01:27:49,390 --> 01:27:51,850
-Show me how the satellites work.
-Okay.

993
01:27:57,356 --> 01:27:59,566
[BEEPING]

994
01:28:01,861 --> 01:28:03,903
[CACKLING]

995
01:28:05,281 --> 01:28:09,659
First, I will turn Gotham into
an icy graveyard...

996
01:28:09,869 --> 01:28:13,872
...then I will pull Batman's heart
from his body...

997
01:28:14,081 --> 01:28:17,083
...and feel it freeze in my hands.

998
01:28:19,503 --> 01:28:21,004
[LAUGHS]

999
01:28:21,172 --> 01:28:22,213
Revenge!

1000
01:28:23,716 --> 01:28:25,216
POISON IVY:
Quickly, Bane.

1001
01:28:25,426 --> 01:28:26,885
Quickly, now.

1002
01:28:34,226 --> 01:28:35,852
[BANE ROARING]

1003
01:28:40,107 --> 01:28:42,233
Let there be light.

1004
01:28:48,574 --> 01:28:50,950
BARBARA:
Only family can be trusted?

1005
01:28:51,327 --> 01:28:53,328
Well...

1006
01:28:53,913 --> 01:28:55,079
...I'm family.

1007
01:29:01,962 --> 01:29:03,880
COMPUTER:
Access denied.

1008
01:29:08,219 --> 01:29:09,844
Access denied.

1009
01:29:21,273 --> 01:29:22,774
Hey.

1010
01:29:31,784 --> 01:29:34,869
I spend my entire life
trying to beat back death.

1011
01:29:39,124 --> 01:29:41,501
Everything I've done,
everything I'm...

1012
01:29:42,169 --> 01:29:44,170
...capable of doing....

1013
01:29:47,675 --> 01:29:49,676
But I can't save you.

1014
01:29:50,886 --> 01:29:53,972
There's no defeat in death...

1015
01:29:54,139 --> 01:29:56,140
...Master Bruce.

1016
01:29:57,518 --> 01:30:00,478
Victory comes in defending...

1017
01:30:00,688 --> 01:30:02,981
...what we know is right...

1018
01:30:03,399 --> 01:30:05,900
...while we still live.

1019
01:30:16,120 --> 01:30:17,662
[ALFRED CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1020
01:30:35,055 --> 01:30:36,848
I love you, old man.

1021
01:30:40,185 --> 01:30:43,021
And I love you too.

1022
01:31:06,086 --> 01:31:07,754
COMPUTER:
Access denied.

1023
01:31:08,213 --> 01:31:10,381
This better be one hell of a secret.

1024
01:31:13,260 --> 01:31:14,719
Access denied.

1025
01:31:18,891 --> 01:31:20,183
BARBARA:
Margaret.

1026
01:31:21,268 --> 01:31:22,685
Margaret.

1027
01:31:27,900 --> 01:31:29,275
COMPUTER:
Access denied.

1028
01:31:36,909 --> 01:31:38,284
Peg.

1029
01:31:42,790 --> 01:31:45,083
COMPUTER:
Access allowed.

1030
01:32:13,320 --> 01:32:16,572
MR. FREEZE: The combined power of
the telescope's reflecting crystals...

1031
01:32:16,782 --> 01:32:19,659
...will complete my freezing engine.

1032
01:32:20,077 --> 01:32:21,285
Yes.

1033
01:32:21,453 --> 01:32:22,829
[BANE GROWLS]

1034
01:32:23,414 --> 01:32:26,249
No matter what they tell you,
Mr. Bane...

1035
01:32:26,458 --> 01:32:29,127
...it is the size of
your gun that counts.

1036
01:32:29,294 --> 01:32:30,837
BANE:
Gun.

1037
01:32:38,804 --> 01:32:39,971
BRUCE:
Where are you going?

1038
01:32:40,139 --> 01:32:42,974
It's not a Batlight, it's a Robin signal.
Ivy's calling me.

1039
01:32:43,183 --> 01:32:45,977
She is Pamela Isley.
She must've stolen Gordon's keys.

1040
01:32:46,145 --> 01:32:48,980
-She changed the signal.
-She did it for me, for love.

1041
01:32:49,148 --> 01:32:50,982
She infected us with pheromones.

1042
01:32:51,191 --> 01:32:53,484
I'm under some kind of magic spell?

1043
01:32:53,694 --> 01:32:54,861
She wants to kill you.

1044
01:32:55,195 --> 01:32:57,697
You'd say anything to keep her
away from me.

1045
01:32:57,948 --> 01:32:59,490
To keep her for yourself.

1046
01:32:59,992 --> 01:33:02,660
You said being a team
means trusting your partner.

1047
01:33:02,870 --> 01:33:07,373
Sometimes counting on someone
else is the only way to win. Remember?

1048
01:33:08,000 --> 01:33:11,711
You weren't talking about partners,
but about being a family.

1049
01:33:12,379 --> 01:33:14,005
So I'm asking you...

1050
01:33:14,173 --> 01:33:17,008
...friend, partner, brother...

1051
01:33:17,885 --> 01:33:20,511
...will you trust me now?

1052
01:33:32,232 --> 01:33:34,901
WOMAN: All the crystals are in place.
LEE: Thank you.

1053
01:33:35,694 --> 01:33:37,361
[LOUD THUMPING]

1054
01:33:44,411 --> 01:33:45,703
Hi!

1055
01:33:45,871 --> 01:33:47,705
Oh. I'm sorry about the door.

1056
01:33:48,665 --> 01:33:49,874
Is the party over?

1057
01:33:50,125 --> 01:33:51,709
BANE:
Over.

1058
01:33:53,003 --> 01:33:54,879
Who is this nutball?

1059
01:33:57,341 --> 01:33:58,883
[SCREAMING]

1060
01:34:10,145 --> 01:34:11,395
[MR. FREEZE LAUGHING]

1061
01:34:13,232 --> 01:34:15,358
BANE:
Bomb.

1062
01:34:17,361 --> 01:34:31,582
Bomb.

1063
01:34:34,419 --> 01:34:36,087
If revenge...

1064
01:34:36,296 --> 01:34:38,673
...is a dish best served cold...

1065
01:34:39,174 --> 01:34:41,676
...then put on your Sunday finest.

1066
01:34:42,261 --> 01:34:45,388
It's time to feast!

1067
01:34:49,601 --> 01:34:51,894
[WHIRRING]

1068
01:34:56,942 --> 01:34:58,150
Tonight...

1069
01:34:58,318 --> 01:35:01,612
...hell freezes over.

1070
01:35:01,780 --> 01:35:03,489
[LAUGHING]

1071
01:35:36,648 --> 01:35:38,858
[ALARM BEEPING]

1072
01:35:39,985 --> 01:35:42,028
ALFRED [ON TV]:
Intruder alert.

1073
01:35:42,279 --> 01:35:43,487
Intruder alert.

1074
01:35:45,741 --> 01:35:47,950
Intruder alert. Identify.

1075
01:35:48,785 --> 01:35:51,245
Uncle Alfred, it's me. Barbara.

1076
01:35:51,663 --> 01:35:54,665
I expected you might find
your way down here, child.

1077
01:35:54,833 --> 01:35:57,293
I programmed my brain algorithms...

1078
01:35:57,502 --> 01:35:58,961
...into the batcomputer...

1079
01:35:59,171 --> 01:36:02,673
...and created a virtual simulation.

1080
01:36:02,966 --> 01:36:05,051
I'd like to help Batman and Robin.

1081
01:36:05,302 --> 01:36:06,886
I anticipated you would...

1082
01:36:07,054 --> 01:36:10,514
...and took the liberty
to create something in your size.

1083
01:36:11,767 --> 01:36:13,851
Suit me up, Uncle Alfred.

1084
01:37:34,766 --> 01:37:36,058
Hi there.

1085
01:37:40,272 --> 01:37:42,940
Is your thumb
the only part of you that's green?

1086
01:37:43,400 --> 01:37:46,235
You will just have to find out.

1087
01:37:46,862 --> 01:37:48,612
ROBIN:
I want us to be together...

1088
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:51,574
...but you must be serious
about turning over a new leaf.

1089
01:37:53,285 --> 01:37:54,368
I need a sign--

1090
01:37:55,245 --> 01:37:57,371
How about "Slippery when wet."

1091
01:37:57,581 --> 01:37:58,914
--of trust.

1092
01:37:59,082 --> 01:38:00,624
Tell me your plan.

1093
01:38:00,876 --> 01:38:02,460
Kiss me and I'll tell you.

1094
01:38:03,378 --> 01:38:05,296
Tell me and I'll kiss you.

1095
01:38:06,673 --> 01:38:11,469
Freeze has taken the new telescope
and turned it into a giant freezing gun.

1096
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:14,430
He's about to turn Gotham
into an ice cube.

1097
01:38:15,682 --> 01:38:17,266
I've got to stop him.

1098
01:38:17,434 --> 01:38:19,769
One kiss, my love.

1099
01:38:20,937 --> 01:38:22,396
For luck.

1100
01:38:35,410 --> 01:38:37,161
Bad luck, I'm afraid.

1101
01:38:37,996 --> 01:38:39,997
Time to die, little Robin.

1102
01:38:43,210 --> 01:38:45,544
I hate to disappoint you...

1103
01:38:49,633 --> 01:38:52,301
...but rubber lips are immune to
your charms.

1104
01:38:59,518 --> 01:39:00,851
See you!

1105
01:39:02,729 --> 01:39:05,523
You're not the only one
who can set a trap, Venus.

1106
01:39:05,941 --> 01:39:09,693
Sorry, my vines have a crush on you.

1107
01:39:16,535 --> 01:39:17,660
[LAUGHING]

1108
01:39:17,828 --> 01:39:18,869
Got to go.

1109
01:39:19,037 --> 01:39:22,498
So many people to kill,
so little time.

1110
01:39:31,967 --> 01:39:33,676
You're about to become compost.

1111
01:39:41,351 --> 01:39:45,229
Using feminine wiles to get what
you want? Trading on your looks?

1112
01:39:45,397 --> 01:39:48,899
Read a book. That passive-aggressive
number went out long ago.

1113
01:39:49,109 --> 01:39:51,193
Chicks like you
give women a bad name.

1114
01:40:02,747 --> 01:40:04,206
[BLADE BUZZING]

1115
01:40:11,590 --> 01:40:15,301
As I told Lady Fries
when I pulled her plug...

1116
01:40:15,886 --> 01:40:17,595
...this is a one-woman show.

1117
01:40:18,013 --> 01:40:19,388
I don't think so.

1118
01:40:41,119 --> 01:40:42,453
Curses!

1119
01:40:42,662 --> 01:40:43,954
No!

1120
01:40:44,122 --> 01:40:45,581
[SCREAMING]

1121
01:40:58,470 --> 01:41:00,095
Freeze is going to ice the city.

1122
01:41:00,305 --> 01:41:01,597
I know.

1123
01:41:01,765 --> 01:41:03,974
-And you are?
-Batgirl.

1124
01:41:04,142 --> 01:41:07,686
That's not P.C.
What about Batperson or Batwoman?

1125
01:41:08,063 --> 01:41:11,315
Bruce, it's me, Barbara.
I found the batcave.

1126
01:41:11,566 --> 01:41:13,025
We must change the locks.

1127
01:41:13,193 --> 01:41:15,361
-She knows who we are.
-We must kill her.

1128
01:41:15,612 --> 01:41:17,863
Yep. We'll kill her later.
We have work to do.

1129
01:41:37,217 --> 01:41:40,135
Let's kick some ice.

1130
01:41:40,679 --> 01:41:51,397
Yes.

1131
01:42:05,036 --> 01:42:08,205
Yes. Yes. Yes.

1132
01:42:23,263 --> 01:42:24,680
[SIRENS WAILING]

1133
01:42:40,739 --> 01:42:42,072
[LAUGHING]

1134
01:43:08,183 --> 01:43:10,434
We have less than 11 minutes
to thaw the city.

1135
01:43:37,962 --> 01:43:39,088
Gotcha!

1136
01:43:40,131 --> 01:43:41,632
Now!

1137
01:43:50,934 --> 01:43:52,101
Shield.

1138
01:44:13,665 --> 01:44:15,332
MR. FREEZE:
I'll finish off the city.

1139
01:44:15,500 --> 01:44:17,751
You kill the kids...

1140
01:44:17,961 --> 01:44:20,504
-...but leave me the bat.
BANE: Bat!

1141
01:44:40,400 --> 01:44:42,359
ROBIN:
No sign of the snowman.

1142
01:44:42,527 --> 01:44:44,319
Maybe he melted.

1143
01:44:44,529 --> 01:44:46,572
No, he's just hibernating.

1144
01:45:01,379 --> 01:45:03,005
[BEEPING]

1145
01:45:04,591 --> 01:45:05,924
These heaters will thaw them.

1146
01:45:09,554 --> 01:45:11,096
[ICE CRACKING]

1147
01:45:13,850 --> 01:45:15,767
I hope you've got
10 million more of those.

1148
01:45:15,935 --> 01:45:18,395
ROBIN: Eight minutes
and they're ice cubes forever.

1149
01:45:18,563 --> 01:45:20,522
Sunlight could reverse
the freezing process.

1150
01:45:20,690 --> 01:45:22,566
-Sunrise isn't for five hours.
-Here.

1151
01:45:22,734 --> 01:45:24,109
It's morning in the Congo.

1152
01:45:24,319 --> 01:45:27,070
BATMAN: We'll relay sunlight--
ROBIN: From below the equator--

1153
01:45:27,238 --> 01:45:29,698
It'll take the satellites
a minute to realign, but....

1154
01:45:30,325 --> 01:45:32,701
-Damn.
-Damn? Damn's not good.

1155
01:45:32,869 --> 01:45:35,579
Those targeting mirrors are frozen.
The beam won't work.

1156
01:45:35,747 --> 01:45:37,247
You thaw the mirrors.

1157
01:46:03,441 --> 01:46:04,942
Tonight's forecast:

1158
01:46:05,109 --> 01:46:06,902
A freeze is coming.

1159
01:46:14,911 --> 01:46:16,119
[SCREAMING]

1160
01:46:21,459 --> 01:46:22,876
Bye-bye.

1161
01:46:35,932 --> 01:46:37,140
I got you!

1162
01:46:39,602 --> 01:46:40,644
[SCREAMING]

1163
01:46:47,652 --> 01:46:49,695
No. I got you.

1164
01:46:55,118 --> 01:46:56,493
[MR. FREEZE LAUGHING]

1165
01:46:57,036 --> 01:46:58,328
MR. FREEZE:
Yes.

1166
01:47:02,959 --> 01:47:04,835
It's one of those days!

1167
01:47:05,003 --> 01:47:06,169
[SCREAMING]

1168
01:47:11,050 --> 01:47:12,676
Yes!

1169
01:47:33,823 --> 01:47:35,198
[BANE ROARING]

1170
01:47:52,383 --> 01:47:53,717
LEE: Yeah!
-Yes.

1171
01:47:58,848 --> 01:48:00,349
LEE:
Dirty fighter, dirty fighter!

1172
01:48:15,114 --> 01:48:16,698
ROBIN:
The tube.

1173
01:48:18,201 --> 01:48:19,785
[BANE SCREAMING]

1174
01:48:31,547 --> 01:48:32,798
LEE:
Yay, Batman!

1175
01:48:36,594 --> 01:48:37,636
LEE:
Oh, no.

1176
01:48:46,229 --> 01:48:48,814
Hey, Freeze. The heat is on.

1177
01:49:02,286 --> 01:49:05,330
BATMAN: You all right down there?
BOTH: Yeah.

1178
01:49:05,540 --> 01:49:06,623
BATMAN:
Here goes.

1179
01:49:34,485 --> 01:49:35,527
[BOTH SCREAMING]

1180
01:49:35,695 --> 01:49:36,778
Hang on.

1181
01:49:46,080 --> 01:49:47,998
[ICE CRACKING]

1182
01:49:51,836 --> 01:49:53,670
Batman, you're doing it!

1183
01:49:55,006 --> 01:49:56,631
BATMAN:
You've lost, Freeze.

1184
01:49:57,175 --> 01:49:58,300
I think not.

1185
01:49:59,677 --> 01:50:01,178
Bombs away, Batman.

1186
01:50:02,513 --> 01:50:04,181
[CACKLING]

1187
01:50:08,186 --> 01:50:09,352
[RUMBLING]

1188
01:50:15,318 --> 01:50:16,735
[GROANING]

1189
01:50:25,536 --> 01:50:29,122
Freeze in hell, Batman!

1190
01:50:39,675 --> 01:50:41,218
[SCREAMING]

1191
01:50:55,942 --> 01:50:58,652
-What should we do now?
-Pray.

1192
01:51:04,534 --> 01:51:06,034
BATMAN:
Hang on!

1193
01:51:08,955 --> 01:51:10,747
Grab onto my belt!

1194
01:51:30,434 --> 01:51:32,978
LEE: Thank you, Batman!
WOMAN: Thank you!

1195
01:51:36,482 --> 01:51:37,983
Need a ride?

1196
01:51:48,494 --> 01:51:50,996
-Most of Gotham's still frozen.
-It's midnight.

1197
01:51:51,414 --> 01:51:53,957
Telescope's gone.
There's no way to thaw the city.

1198
01:51:54,208 --> 01:51:57,252
The satellites could do it,
but it'd take a computer genius.

1199
01:51:57,420 --> 01:51:58,461
I'm on it.

1200
01:51:59,088 --> 01:52:00,338
BATGIRL:
No, I'm on it.

1201
01:52:06,429 --> 01:52:07,804
Have to do it upside down.

1202
01:52:07,972 --> 01:52:10,473
Men! Everything the hard way.

1203
01:52:13,102 --> 01:52:15,145
ROBIN:
You're pretty good at this, little girl.

1204
01:52:15,646 --> 01:52:19,232
Well, watch and learn, little boy.

1205
01:52:33,873 --> 01:52:35,332
[ICE CRACKING]

1206
01:53:26,217 --> 01:53:29,052
Looks like it's gonna be a beautiful day.

1207
01:53:36,560 --> 01:53:39,813
BATMAN: I'm taking you back
to Arkham Asylum.

1208
01:53:40,731 --> 01:53:42,232
Go on.

1209
01:53:43,067 --> 01:53:44,401
Kill me too.

1210
01:53:44,610 --> 01:53:46,361
Just as you killed my wife.

1211
01:53:46,529 --> 01:53:48,071
I didn't kill your wife.

1212
01:53:53,119 --> 01:53:57,122
[ON SCREEN] As I told Lady Fries
when I pulled her plug...

1213
01:53:57,456 --> 01:53:59,833
...this is a one-woman show.

1214
01:54:01,419 --> 01:54:02,752
[SCREAMING]

1215
01:54:05,589 --> 01:54:07,465
BATMAN:
But she's not dead.

1216
01:54:08,259 --> 01:54:10,135
We found her, restored her.

1217
01:54:10,636 --> 01:54:12,929
She's still frozen alive...

1218
01:54:13,139 --> 01:54:14,973
...waiting for you to find a cure.

1219
01:54:16,267 --> 01:54:17,934
She lives?

1220
01:54:18,144 --> 01:54:20,103
-Yes.
-She lives.

1221
01:54:20,271 --> 01:54:23,606
But vengeance isn't power.
Anyone can take a life.

1222
01:54:24,108 --> 01:54:25,650
But to give life...

1223
01:54:26,152 --> 01:54:28,987
...that's true power.
A power you once had.

1224
01:54:30,281 --> 01:54:32,115
She's alive.

1225
01:54:37,788 --> 01:54:39,456
So I'm asking you.

1226
01:54:40,458 --> 01:54:42,000
Victor Fries...

1227
01:54:42,877 --> 01:54:44,794
...help me save another life.

1228
01:54:45,171 --> 01:54:48,298
Show me how to cure
Macgregor's Syndrome, stage one.

1229
01:54:48,674 --> 01:54:52,510
And maybe you can also save the life
of the man your wife once loved.

1230
01:54:53,471 --> 01:54:55,597
He's still inside you, Victor.

1231
01:54:56,515 --> 01:54:57,807
Buried...

1232
01:54:57,975 --> 01:55:00,185
...deep beneath the snow.

1233
01:55:02,688 --> 01:55:04,314
Will you help me...

1234
01:55:05,816 --> 01:55:07,317
...doctor?

1235
01:55:31,675 --> 01:55:33,676
Take two of these...

1236
01:55:34,929 --> 01:55:36,846
...and call me in the morning.

1237
01:55:47,441 --> 01:55:50,401
BATMAN: I'll have your wife
moved to the lab at Arkham.

1238
01:55:50,569 --> 01:55:53,029
You'll be able to continue
your research there.

1239
01:56:16,262 --> 01:56:18,513
All we can do now is wait...

1240
01:56:19,265 --> 01:56:21,099
...and hope.

1241
01:56:30,025 --> 01:56:31,401
[THUNDER CRASHING]

1242
01:56:34,738 --> 01:56:36,114
POISON IVY:
He loves me.

1243
01:56:36,740 --> 01:56:38,491
He loves me not.

1244
01:56:40,035 --> 01:56:41,619
He loves me.

1245
01:56:42,913 --> 01:56:44,914
He loves me not.

1246
01:56:47,293 --> 01:56:49,127
He loves me.

1247
01:56:50,754 --> 01:56:52,589
He loves me not.

1248
01:56:55,092 --> 01:56:56,509
He loves me.

1249
01:56:58,429 --> 01:56:59,637
MR. FREEZE:
Not!

1250
01:57:01,599 --> 01:57:03,099
Surprise.

1251
01:57:03,267 --> 01:57:05,268
I'm your new cellmate.

1252
01:57:07,521 --> 01:57:11,149
And I've come
to make your life a living hell.

1253
01:57:11,650 --> 01:57:14,652
Prepare for a bitter harvest.

1254
01:57:18,616 --> 01:57:21,951
Winter has come at last.

1255
01:57:57,655 --> 01:57:58,988
[CLEARING THROAT]

1256
01:58:03,077 --> 01:58:04,619
Alfred.

1257
01:58:07,498 --> 01:58:08,539
Are you...?

1258
01:58:08,707 --> 01:58:13,336
Rather disappointed at how poorly
I have taught you proper housekeeping.

1259
01:58:13,837 --> 01:58:15,880
And quite well, it seems!

1260
01:58:16,090 --> 01:58:17,465
Thanks to you, son.

1261
01:58:17,675 --> 01:58:19,842
Thanks to you all.

1262
01:58:20,094 --> 01:58:21,678
Well done, Bruce.

1263
01:58:22,012 --> 01:58:24,097
You too. Well done.

1264
01:58:25,516 --> 01:58:27,016
I got one question.

1265
01:58:27,351 --> 01:58:31,020
When we fell off the telescope,
why didn't you try and save us?

1266
01:58:31,188 --> 01:58:33,523
It's the first time I fell
and you weren't there.

1267
01:58:34,024 --> 01:58:35,525
I figured you could handle it.

1268
01:58:35,693 --> 01:58:40,405
You know, sometimes counting on
somebody else is the only way to win.

1269
01:58:43,117 --> 01:58:46,536
Excuse me. I'm the one
who kicked Ivy's botanical butt.

1270
01:58:46,704 --> 01:58:48,037
Yeah, that was me.

1271
01:58:48,205 --> 01:58:50,707
I did it all by myself. That was me.

1272
01:58:50,874 --> 01:58:53,209
You are going back to school.

1273
01:58:53,377 --> 01:58:55,044
You'll never win this argument.

1274
01:59:00,050 --> 01:59:01,384
Partners?

1275
01:59:06,348 --> 01:59:18,443
Partners.

1276
01:59:21,905 --> 01:59:24,073
We're going to need a bigger cave.

1277
02:04:47,689 --> 02:04:49,690
[ENGLISH SDH]

